The cyclone season in Mauritius normally runs from November to May. The Mauritian authorities have advised that a cyclone warning class III is in force for the island of Rodrigues. There is currently no cyclone warning in place for Mauritius itself. You should continue to monitor and follow the advice of the Mauritius Meteorological Services.
Drug trafficking carries severe penalties.
Around 140,000 British tourists visit Mauritius every year. Most visits are trouble free.
Terrorist attacks in Mauritius can’t be ruled out. See Terrorism
The Overseas Business Risk service offers information and advice for British companies operating overseas on how to manage political, economic, and business security-related risks.
If you’re abroad and you need emergency help from the UK government, contact the nearest British embassy, consulate or high commission.
Take out comprehensive travel and medical insurance before you travel. 
